<h2 id="what-is-birdeye">🔍 What Is Birdeye?</h2>

Birdeye is an all-in-one experience platform that combines reputation management, customer communications, and local SEO tools. Founded in 2012, the company has evolved from a simple review monitoring tool into a comprehensive platform serving over 100,000 businesses.

For med spas specifically, Birdeye offers HIPAA-compliant messaging, review generation workflows that integrate with practice management systems, and AI-powered response suggestions trained on healthcare contexts. The platform pulls reviews from 200+ sites including Google, Yelp, Facebook, RealSelf, and Healthgrades — all into a single dashboard.

The 2026 version introduces several meaningful updates: enhanced AI response generation that understands aesthetic procedure terminology, deeper integrations with med spa-specific EMRs like Aesthetic Record and PatientNow, and improved competitive benchmarking at the hyperlocal level.

<h2 id="our-experience">💼 Our Experience Managing Thousands of Locations</h2>

Our team has implemented Birdeye across med spa groups ranging from 3 locations to 47 locations. We've also evaluated it against competitors like Podium, Reputation.com, and NiceJob for aesthetics businesses specifically.

The deployment reality: expect 2-3 weeks for proper setup at multi-location groups. This includes connecting all review sources, training front desk staff on the review request workflow, configuring location-specific response templates, and establishing escalation protocols for negative reviews mentioning complications.

At one 12-location med spa group, we tracked a 52% increase in Google review volume within the first quarter. More importantly, the average star rating improved from 4.2 to 4.6 as the automated review requests reached satisfied clients who wouldn't have left reviews otherwise.

